Peter Dada, Akure The Ondo State Governor, Mr Rotimi Akeredolu said he would not react to the statement credited to the Senate President, Ahmed Lawan, on the issue of insecurity in the country, saying he was not interested in engaging any person or group of persons in media war on the issue, especially the ones that concern the South-West. READ ALSO: Division among bandits delays abducted Niger schoolboys’ release The Governor stated this through his Special Assistant on New Media, Mr Olabode Olatunde. He said, “At the risk of being repetitive, the Governor Akeredolu-led South-West Governors will not go into the arena of media conflict with crisis entrepreneurs and divisionists.” READ ALSO: Okorocha boasts of presidential bid, 14 ex-aides get N70m bail